# .aiexclude — agent navigation hint, NOT a security boundary.
#
# This file is honored by AI coding agents that respect gitignore-style
# exclusion (Continue, Aider, Cursor's `ignore` settings, etc.). When an
# agent is asked to work on a *specific* provider file, this list tells
# the agent which sibling files it does NOT need to load into context.
#
# Always include open-sse/AGENT-INDEX.md (this directory's curated index)
# in agent context -- it is small (~30 KB) and lets the agent navigate the
# provider surface without loading every executor.
#
# Format: standard gitignore globs. Lines starting with `#` are comments.
# This file is OPT-IN for agents; some agents ignore it. The
# AGENT-INDEX.md is the primary navigability surface; this is a hint
# for agents that honour ignore-files.
#
# Maintenance: keep this file small and focused. If you find yourself
# adding many globs, the underlying problem is too large a context
# surface -- file a follow-up issue rather than maintaining a long list
# here.

# Keep the curated executor index always available -- it is the
# navigation index for everything below.
!open-sse/AGENT-INDEX.md

# Per-provider executors: agents working on `cursor.ts` should not load
# every other executor into context. Encourage the agent to read the
# curated index first, then open only the executor the task is about.
open-sse/executors/*.ts
!open-sse/executors/index.ts
!open-sse/executors/base.ts
!open-sse/executors/default.ts